Nested If statment?
//it's just an if statement inside of an if statement
Why do we need the nested if statements?
When we have to test 1 condition based on another condition
When we have to do a further check
If you have one condition that is dependant upon another condition



if(boolean condition) { outer if statement
	if(boolean condition){ inner if statement
	}
}


Assigment operators: =
Arithmetic : +, -, *, /, %
Relational: >, >=, <,<=, ==, !=
Logical: &&, ||, !
Logical and &&

true && true True
true && false False
false && true False
false && false False






